### Blending Two Walking Cycles

Walk A has a 1-second period. Walk B has a 0.7-second period (faster stride). Blend them to shift gait speed.

```scheme
(define (walk-a-x t)
  (* 30.0 (sin (* 6.28 t))))

(define (walk-b-x t)
  (* 30.0 (sin (* 8.97 t))))

(define (blend-x ax bx w)
  (+ (* ax (- 1.0 w))
     (* bx w)))

(motion
 (at 0.0
     (pose
      (entity 'leg
              (joint 'thigh
                     (blend-x (walk-a-x 0.0) (walk-b-x 0.0) 0.2)
                     0.0))))
 (at 0.5
     (pose
      (entity 'leg
              (joint 'thigh
                     (blend-x (walk-a-x 0.5) (walk-b-x 0.5) 0.2)
                     0.0))))
 (at 1.0
     (pose
      (entity 'leg
              (joint 'thigh
                     (blend-x (walk-a-x 1.0) (walk-b-x 1.0) 0.2)
                     0.0)))))
```

[VISUAL: Thigh swing frequency slightly faster than walk-a alone.]

