### Phase-Locked Blend

Match the phase of two periodic motions before blending to avoid a beat-frequency wobble.

```scheme
(define (wave-y t phase)
  (* 30.0 (sin (+ (* 5.0 t) phase))))

(define (blend-x ax bx w)
  (+ (* ax (- 1.0 w))
     (* bx w)))

(motion
 (at 0.0
     (pose
      (entity 'hand
              (transform
               100.0
               (blend-x (wave-y 0.0 0.0) (wave-y 0.0 0.0) 0.0)
               0.0))))
 (at 1.0
     (pose
      (entity 'hand
              (transform
               100.0
               (blend-x (wave-y 1.0 0.0) (wave-y 1.0 0.0) 1.0)
               0.0)))))
```

Both animations share the same frequency and phase—blend is seamless even at intermediate weights.

[VISUAL: Hand waves continuously; blend weight has no visible effect because the streams are identical.]

