### Blending with Velocity Preservation

When switching from a fast animation to a slow one, carry forward the velocity at the transition instant to avoid a visible \"brake.\"

```scheme
(define (fast-x t)
  (* 200.0 t))

(define (slow-x t)
  (* 50.0 t))

(define (blend-x ax bx w)
  (+ (* ax (- 1.0 w))
     (* bx w)))

(motion
 (at 0.0
     (pose
      (entity 'ball
              (transform
               (blend-x (fast-x 0.0) (slow-x 0.0) 0.0)
               100.0
               0.0))))
 (at 0.5
     (pose
      (entity 'ball
              (transform
               (blend-x (fast-x 0.5) (slow-x 0.5) 0.5)
               100.0
               0.0))))
 (at 1.0
     (pose
      (entity 'ball
              (transform
               (blend-x (fast-x 1.0) (slow-x 1.0) 1.0)
               100.0
               0.0)))))
```

[VISUAL: Ball decelerates smoothly as the blend weight increases, no sharp corner in the path.]

*[needs: explicit velocity matching at transition instant for true momentum preservation]*

