---


### Blending Rotation Shortest-Path

Linear blend of angles can spin the long way. Wrap angle difference to `[-180, 180]` first.

```scheme
(define (angle-diff a b)
  (let ((d (- b a)))
    (cond
     ((> d 180.0) (- d 360.0))
     ((< d -180.0) (+ d 360.0))
     (else d))))

(define (blend-angle ax bx w)
  (+ ax (* (angle-diff ax bx) w)))

(motion
 (pose
  (entity 'arrow
          (transform
           150.0
           150.0
           (blend-angle 10.0 350.0 0.5)))))
```

At `w=0.5`, angle is `0.0` (halfway on the short arc from 10° to 350°), not `180.0`.

[VISUAL: Arrow points north, having rotated -10° instead of +170°.]

