### Multi-Layer Blend Tree

Blend `idle` and `walk`, then blend that result with `jump`.

```scheme
(define (blend-x ax bx w)
  (+ (* ax (- 1.0 w))
     (* bx w)))

(define idle-y 100.0)
(define walk-y 110.0)
(define jump-y 180.0)

(motion
 (pose
  (entity 'figure
          (transform
           100.0
           (blend-x (blend-x idle-y walk-y 0.6)
                    jump-y
                    0.3)
           0.0))))
```

First blend: `0.4*100 + 0.6*110 = 106`. Second blend: `0.7*106 + 0.3*180 = 128.2`.

