### Inertialized Blend

Inject an offset that decays to zero, smoothing the position discontinuity at the transition instant.

```scheme
(define (ease-out-cubic x)
  (let ((u (- 1.0 x)))
    (- 1.0 (* u u u))))

(define (blend-x ax bx w)
  (+ (* ax (- 1.0 w))
     (* bx w)))

(define transition-offset 30.0)

(motion
 (at 0.0
     (pose
      (entity 'box
              (transform
               (+ (blend-x 100.0 200.0 0.0)
                  (* transition-offset (- 1.0 (ease-out-cubic 0.0))))
               100.0
               0.0))))
 (at 0.3
     (pose
      (entity 'box
              (transform
               (+ (blend-x 100.0 200.0 0.5)
                  (* transition-offset (- 1.0 (ease-out-cubic 0.5))))
               100.0
               0.0))))
 (at 0.6
     (pose
      (entity 'box
              (transform
               (+ (blend-x 100.0 200.0 1.0)
                  (* transition-offset (- 1.0 (ease-out-cubic 1.0))))
               100.0
               0.0)))))
```

[VISUAL: Box starts with a 30-pixel overshoot that decays cubically as it blends from 100 to 200.]

