### Blend Gesture Timing Curves

Two gestures with different easing. Blend the timing functions themselves, not just the endpoints.

```scheme
(define (ease-a x)
  (* x x))

(define (ease-b x)
  (- (* 2.0 x) (* x x)))

(define (blend-x ax bx w)
  (+ (* ax (- 1.0 w))
     (* bx w)))

(define (blended-ease x w)
  (blend-x (ease-a x) (ease-b x) w))

(motion
 (at 0.0
     (pose
      (entity 'hand
              (transform
               (+ 50.0 (* 200.0 (blended-ease 0.0 0.0)))
               100.0
               0.0))))
 (at 1.0
     (pose
      (entity 'hand
              (transform
               (+ 50.0 (* 200.0 (blended-ease 1.0 0.0)))
               100.0
               0.0)))))
```

At `w=0.0`, gesture follows `ease-a` (slow start). At `w=1.0`, follows `ease-b` (fast start, slow end).

[VISUAL: Hand reaches target with ease-a acceleration profile.]

