### Blend Walk with Different Step Lengths

Walk A: 100-pixel stride. Walk B: 60-pixel stride. Blend the horizontal displacement per cycle.

```scheme
(define (walk-a-x t)
  (* 100.0 t))

(define (walk-b-x t)
  (* 60.0 t))

(define (blend-x ax bx w)
  (+ (* ax (- 1.0 w))
     (* bx w)))

(motion
 (at 0.0
     (pose
      (entity 'walker
              (transform
               (blend-x (walk-a-x 0.0) (walk-b-x 0.0) 0.7)
               100.0
               0.0))))
 (at 2.0
     (pose
      (entity 'walker
              (transform
               (blend-x (walk-a-x 2.0) (walk-b-x 2.0) 0.7)
               100.0
               0.0)))))
```

Blended stride: `0.3*200 + 0.7*120 = 144` pixels in 2 seconds.

[VISUAL: Walker moves forward at the averaged pace.]

