### Crossfade with Anticipation

Inject a small counter-motion before the blend to prepare for the transition.

```scheme
(define (anticipate x)
  (cond
   ((< x 0.2) (* -0.5 (/ x 0.2)))
   (else (/ (- x 0.2) 0.8))))

(define (blend-x ax bx w)
  (+ (* ax (- 1.0 w))
     (* bx w)))

(motion
 (at 0.0
     (pose
      (entity 'figure
              (transform
               (blend-x 100.0 250.0 (anticipate 0.0))
               100.0
               0.0))))
 (at 0.2
     (pose
      (entity 'figure
              (transform
               (blend-x 100.0 250.0 (anticipate 0.2))
               100.0
               0.0))))
 (at 1.0
     (pose
      (entity 'figure
              (transform
               (blend-x 100.0 250.0 (anticipate 1.0))
               100.0
               0.0)))))
```

[VISUAL: Figure shifts slightly left before gliding right—anticipation makes the transition feel intentional.]

