### Blend Two Wind-Force Directions

Wind A blows east. Wind B blows north. Blend the force vector to get a northeast wind.

```scheme
(define wind-a-x 50.0)
(define wind-a-y 0.0)
(define wind-b-x 0.0)
(define wind-b-y 50.0)

(define (blend-x ax bx w)
  (+ (* ax (- 1.0 w))
     (* bx w)))

(define (flag-x t wx)
  (+ 100.0 (* wx 0.01 t t)))

(define (flag-y t wy)
  (+ 150.0 (* wy 0.01 t t)))

(motion
 (at 0.0
     (pose
      (entity 'flag
              (transform
               (flag-x 0.0 (blend-x wind-a-x wind-b-x 0.5))
               (flag-y 0.0 (blend-x wind-a-y wind-b-y 0.5))
               0.0))))
 (at 2.0
     (pose
      (entity 'flag
              (transform
               (flag-x 2.0 (blend-x wind-a-x wind-b-x 0.5))
               (flag-y 2.0 (blend-x wind-a-y wind-b-y 0.5))
               0.0)))))
```

[VISUAL: Flag drifts northeast as equal weights mix east and north wind.]

